The TEB is divided into regions based on morphology. The outer cap cell and myoepithelial layer is designated as regions 1–4. The inner body cell and luminal layer is designated as regions 5–8. Each region has independent outflux values resulting from net proliferation and yielding to total fluxes toward the mature duct. Non-zero fluxes included in the Base Model (Model 1) are shown in red, additional basal to luminal fluxes included in the subsequent models (Models 2–4) are depicted in grey. The rate at which the duct elongates is determined by the total flux and the length (
l
) of a mature myoepithelial cell in 2D.
